~OLCommand :~RS grepu
~OLUsage   :~RS grepu <pattern>

This command allows you to search for a user whose name has the <pattern>
in it. The pattern can have the wildcards ?, for a single letter match,
or * for multiple letter matches. For example:

.grepu an?? will match Andy, Andi, Anne and so on.
.grepu an* will match Andy, Anne, Another, Anthony and so on.

You cannot have the wildcards placed together, such as ?*, *? or **.
